{"key":"processedPost-8576662","value":{"id":8576662,"first":8576165,"last":8577097,"when":1214746830,"utime":"06/29/08 04:40 PM","content":"There's a few paragraphs on lighting at the bottom of the <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Terrarium-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">terrarium tek page</a> on my site.&nbsp; I've typed it all here many times too.<br /><br />Light is NOT just to tell the fruits which way to go.&nbsp; Light is an integral part of a healthy environment for mushrooms, as well as people.&nbsp; Mushrooms have circadian rhythms also, just like people.&nbsp; A slight rise in temperature during the daylight hours will also help.&nbsp; Bright light is far more effective then dim light.<br /><br />It need not be exactly 12/12, but try to get close.&nbsp; If all my timers are in use, I'll simply plug the lights in when I get up in the morning, and unplug them after dinner in the evening.&nbsp; It's not like mj where seconds count.<br />RR","title":"Re: lighting"}}